# Repository Licensing Declaration

This repository applies the shared repository licensing policy published at:

- Policy source: https://github.com/FOP-Oksana-Dubinetska/repository-licensing-policy
- Git submodule path: .licensing-policy/
- Pinned policy version: $POLICY_VERSION (6e4c262)

The policy submodule is incorporated by reference.

This file is the root licensing declaration for this repository.

## Default licensing map

Unless a more specific third-party notice, subtree notice, file-level notice, or project-specific override applies:

| Scope | Default license |
|---|---|
| Original articles, prose, documentation, publication sources, research notes, and original non-brand editorial materials | CC-BY-SA-4.0 |
| Original source code, scripts, tests, examples, reusable schemas, reusable templates, and build helpers | MIT |
| Names, logos, trademarks, brand assets, visual identity elements, project identity, and studio identity | No license granted; all rights reserved |
| Third-party materials | Their original upstream licenses and notices |

## Project-specific overrides

See LICENSING-OVERRIDES.md if that file exists.

If LICENSING-OVERRIDES.md does not exist, this repository declares no project-specific overrides.

## Precedence

Where multiple notices apply, use the following order:

1. mandatory third-party upstream terms and notices;
2. file-level notices and SPDX identifiers;
3. subtree-specific LICENSE, LICENSE.md, or NOTICE files;
4. LICENSING-OVERRIDES.md;
5. the default licensing map above.

A project-specific override may clarify or replace a default only for material owned by the repository rights holder. It cannot weaken or replace third-party upstream obligations.

## Reference license texts

Reference license texts are available through the pinned policy submodule:

- .licensing-policy/LICENSES/CC-BY-SA-4.0.txt
- .licensing-policy/LICENSES/MIT.txt

## Branding

No permission to reuse names, logos, trademarks, brand assets, visual identity elements, project identity, or studio identity is granted unless explicitly stated in writing.
